    contentBody: `Memorial Day is a federal holiday observed on the last Monday of May, dedicated to honoring the men and women who have died while serving in the United States Armed Forces. Originally known as Decoration Day, the holiday originated after the Civil War when communities began decorating the graves of fallen soldiers with flowers and flags.

The first widely recognized Decoration Day was observed on May 30, 1868, when General John A. Logan of the Grand Army of the Republic called for a nationwide day of remembrance. The date was chosen because it was not the anniversary of any particular battle, making it a universal day of mourning. Over time, the holiday expanded to honor all American military personnel who died in service, not just Civil War soldiers.

In 1971, Congress established Memorial Day as a federal holiday to be observed on the last Monday of May, creating a three-day weekend. In 2026, Memorial Day falls on Monday, May 25. This long weekend is often considered the unofficial start of summer, with many families using it as the first beach trip, pool opening, or outdoor barbecue of the season.

The National Moment of Remembrance, established by Congress in 2000, asks Americans to pause at 3:00 PM local time on Memorial Day for one minute of silence to honor those who have died in military service. Many cities and towns hold Memorial Day parades featuring veterans, active military personnel, marching bands, and civic organizations. The ceremony at Arlington National Cemetery includes laying a wreath at the Tomb of the Unknown Soldier.

Beyond remembrance, Memorial Day weekend has become one of the most popular travel weekends of the year. The three-day weekend provides an opportunity for short getaways, road trips, and family gatherings. Beach towns, lake communities, and national parks see significant increases in visitors. Hotels, campgrounds, and rental properties in vacation destinations often fill up weeks in advance.

Memorial Day is also associated with significant retail sales. Many stores offer Memorial Day sales on furniture, appliances, mattresses, and clothing, making it a popular shopping weekend. Auto dealerships frequently run special promotions. For budget-conscious shoppers, Memorial Day sales provide some of the best prices between post-holiday winter clearances and the Black Friday season.`,
