    contentBody: `Labor Day is a federal holiday observed on the first Monday of September, celebrating the contributions and achievements of American workers. The holiday was created by the labor movement in the late 19th century and became a federal holiday in 1894. It honors the social and economic achievements of workers and is traditionally considered the unofficial end of summer.

The origins of Labor Day trace back to the labor union movement of the 1880s. The Central Labor Union in New York City organized the first Labor Day parade on September 5, 1882, when approximately 10,000 workers marched from City Hall to Union Square. The idea spread to other cities, and states began passing legislation to recognize the holiday. Following a pivotal railroad strike in 1894, President Grover Cleveland signed legislation making Labor Day a federal holiday.

In 2026, Labor Day falls on Monday, September 7, creating a three-day weekend that many Americans use for final summer activities. Pools and beaches that operated on summer schedules often close after Labor Day weekend. Campgrounds and vacation rentals see their last big rush of the summer season, and many families plan end-of-summer trips to squeeze in one more adventure before school routines resume.

The long weekend is one of the busiest travel periods of the year, rivaling Thanksgiving and the Fourth of July. Highways, airports, and popular destinations experience heavy traffic, particularly on Friday afternoon and Saturday as people head to their weekend plans, and on Monday evening as they return home. Planning travel early and allowing extra time for delays can reduce the stress of Labor Day travel.

Labor Day marks a cultural transition in American life. Schools that have not already started typically begin classes the week after Labor Day. Fashion tradition holds that white clothing should not be worn after Labor Day, though this "rule" has relaxed considerably in modern times. Fall activities like football season, apple picking, and leaf peeping come into focus as summer fades.

Retail sales on Labor Day weekend are significant. Stores offer promotions on summer clearance items, back-to-school supplies, mattresses, appliances, and outdoor furniture. Car dealerships often run Labor Day sales events to clear current-year inventory before new models arrive. For shoppers, this weekend provides excellent values on a wide range of products.`,
