    contentBody: `Mother's Day is celebrated on the second Sunday of May each year in the United States, honoring mothers, motherhood, and maternal bonds. In 2026, Mother's Day falls on Sunday, May 10. The holiday is one of the highest-grossing consumer holidays in the country, with Americans spending over $35 billion annually on gifts, dining, and experiences for their mothers.

The modern American Mother's Day was established through the efforts of Anna Jarvis, who organized the first official Mother's Day celebration in 1908 at a church in Grafton, West Virginia, to honor her own mother. Jarvis campaigned tirelessly for official recognition, and in 1914, President Woodrow Wilson signed a proclamation designating the second Sunday in May as Mother's Day. Ironically, Jarvis later became critical of the holiday's commercialization and spent much of her later life trying to remove it from the calendar.

Gift-giving is a central part of Mother's Day celebrations. The most popular gifts include greeting cards, flowers, special outings, clothing, jewelry, gift cards, and personal care items. Flowers remain the classic Mother's Day gift, with carnations being the traditional choice. Pink and red carnations represent a living mother, while white carnations honor a mother who has passed away. Today, roses, tulips, and mixed bouquets are equally popular choices.

Brunch and dinner outings make Mother's Day the busiest restaurant day of the year. Restaurants across the country offer special Mother's Day menus and prix fixe options. Reservations should be made at least two to three weeks in advance, as popular brunch spots fill up quickly. Many families opt to prepare a special meal at home, allowing Mom to relax while others handle the cooking and cleanup.

Personalized and experience-based gifts have gained popularity in recent years. Spa treatments, cooking classes, concert tickets, and weekend getaways offer memorable experiences that go beyond physical gifts. Handmade gifts from children, such as cards, artwork, and breakfast in bed, are often the most treasured Mother's Day presents regardless of cost.

For those who live far from their mothers, planning is especially important. Gift delivery services for flowers and specialty items should be ordered at least a week in advance to guarantee Mother's Day delivery. Video calls can supplement physical gifts, allowing families to share the day together despite the distance.`,
