    contentBody: `Presidents Day is a federal holiday observed on the third Monday of February, originally established to honor George Washington's birthday. In 2027, Presidents Day falls on Monday, February 15. While the holiday is officially designated as Washington's Birthday in federal law, it is commonly known as Presidents Day and is widely regarded as a celebration of all U.S. presidents.

The holiday has its roots in the celebration of George Washington's birthday on February 22, which was an unofficial national holiday for much of the 19th century. In 1879, Congress made Washington's Birthday an official federal holiday, making it the first to honor an individual American. When the Uniform Monday Holiday Act of 1971 moved several holidays to create three-day weekends, Washington's Birthday was shifted to the third Monday of February.

The shift in date and the growing association with Abraham Lincoln's birthday, February 12, led to the popular adoption of the name Presidents Day. Retailers embraced the broader name to promote sales, and the public followed. Today, many Americans use the holiday to honor the office of the presidency and all who have served in it, from Washington to the current occupant of the Oval Office.

The three-day weekend created by Presidents Day makes it a popular time for short vacations and getaways. Ski resorts in New England, the Rocky Mountains, and the Pacific Northwest see increased bookings as families take advantage of the long weekend during peak ski season. Beach destinations in the South also attract visitors seeking a warm-weather escape from winter.

Presidents Day is one of the biggest retail sale events of the year. Furniture stores, mattress retailers, appliance dealers, and car dealerships offer significant discounts during Presidents Day weekend. The tradition of Presidents Day sales has become so established that many consumers specifically wait for this weekend to make large purchases. Electronics, clothing, and home improvement items are also commonly discounted.

Schools in many states observe Presidents Day as a holiday, giving students a day off and providing families with an opportunity for educational activities. Visiting presidential libraries, historic sites, and monuments is a meaningful way to spend the holiday. Mount Vernon, Monticello, the Lincoln Memorial, and the presidential libraries scattered across the country all offer special Presidents Day programming.`,
