    metaTitle: "How Many Days Until Veterans Day 2026? Countdown | ToolCalcs",
    metaDesc: "Count down to Veterans Day 2026. See how many days until Wednesday, November 11, 2026, with our live countdown timer.",
    contentBody: `Veterans Day is a federal holiday observed on November 11 each year, honoring all Americans who have served in the United States Armed Forces. Unlike Memorial Day, which specifically honors those who died in military service, Veterans Day pays tribute to all military veterans, both living and deceased. The holiday coincides with Armistice Day and Remembrance Day, observed in other countries to mark the end of World War I hostilities on November 11, 1918.

The original Armistice Day was proclaimed by President Woodrow Wilson in 1919 to honor the heroes of World War I. Congress made it a legal federal holiday in 1938. After World War II and the Korean War, the holiday was renamed Veterans Day in 1954 to honor all American veterans, not just those who served in World War I.

In 2026, Veterans Day falls on a Wednesday, November 11. When Veterans Day falls midweek, federal employees may receive the day off on Wednesday, while some private employers choose to observe it on the nearest Monday or Friday to create a long weekend. Schools may or may not close, depending on the district.

Veterans Day ceremonies take place at war memorials, cemeteries, and public spaces across the country. The principal national ceremony occurs at Arlington National Cemetery, where a wreath is laid at the Tomb of the Unknown Soldier. The ceremony includes a moment of silence at 11:00 AM, marking the exact time the armistice took effect in 1918. Many communities hold parades, flag-raising ceremonies, and public programs featuring speakers, military demonstrations, and musical performances.

Many businesses offer Veterans Day discounts and free meals to active-duty service members and veterans. National restaurant chains, retail stores, and entertainment venues participate in these appreciation programs. Veterans should carry their military ID, DD-214, or other proof of service to take advantage of these offers. Lists of participating businesses are widely published online in the days leading up to November 11.

The holiday serves as a moment for national reflection on the sacrifices made by military service members and their families. Schools and community organizations often use the occasion to teach younger generations about military history, the meaning of service, and the importance of supporting veterans. Letter-writing campaigns, care package drives, and visits to veterans' hospitals are common volunteer activities around Veterans Day.`,
